metadata.name: Last Smile
metadata.description:
It was not the first time I see her smile.

But her smile that day was so bright. As if it was the brightest star in the sky.

But at that time I was too young to know. That stars shine brightest before they die. 
Too young to know what she hid behind that smile. So I smiled back happily, said nothing and let her go.

It was the last time I saw her smile.
It was the last time I saw her.
